28/04/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President Ion Iliescu met on Tuesday (27 April) with his Greek counterpart, Costas Stephanopoulos, who is making an official visit to Romania. The two officials commended developments in bilateral relations and co-operation at the regional level and pledged to continue joint efforts to promote stability. Stephanopoulos expressed satisfaction with Romania's efforts towards EU membership and pledged Greek support for ensuring the current accession timetable is observed. (ANA, MPA, Rompres - 27/04/04)
